{
  "title": "Mustard Mousse for Ham",
  "instructions": {
    "1": "Dissolve gelatin in 2 tablespoons cold water in a small bowl; transfer to a blender. Add sugar, vinegar, 1/3 cup water, mustard powder, and salt; blend until smooth. Add eggs; blend until smooth.",
    "2": "Place a mixing bowl over a pot of boiling water; pour mustard mixture into bowl. Cook and stir until thick like a custard. Remove from heat; cool completely.",
    "3": "Beat whipping cream in a separate bowl with an electric mixer until soft peaks form. Fold whipped cream into mustard mixture.",
    "4": "Lightly grease a 1-quart ring mold; pour in mustard-cream mixture. Chill in refrigerator overnight. Serve with ham."
  },
